   <p><strong>What does it mean:&nbsp;</strong>The square of the hypotenuse of a triangle is equal to the sum of the squares of its legs. &nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
   <p><strong>History:&nbsp;</strong>Though attributed to Pythagoras, it is not certain that he was the first person to prove it. The first clear proof came from Euclid, and it is possible the concept was known 1000 years before Pythagoras by the Babylonians!</p>
   <p><strong>Importance:&nbsp;</strong>The Pythagorean theorem forms the basis of trigonometry and, when applied to arithmetic, it connects the fields of algebra and geometry. Without it, accurate surveying, map making, and navigation would be impossible.</p>
